    id: "RULE_ART_0464",
    subject: "Test pressures",
    contextLocation: "Ontario",
    constraintType: "Prohibited",
    value: "(1) Except as provided in Sentences (2) and (3) and Article 4.4.6.6., piping systems shall be pressure tested at pressures of not less than 350 kPa (gauge) or 1.5 times the maximum operating pressure, whichever is greater. (2) Test pressures exceeding 700 kPa (gauge) shall not be permitted except when the piping system is designed for such pressures. (3) Where test pressures exceed the design pressures for pumps or similar components included in the piping system being tested, such pumps or components shall be isolated from the remainder of the system.",
