    subject: "Overhead piping",
    contextLocation: "Ontario",
    constraintType: "Minimum",
    value: "(1) Overhead piping for flammable liquids or combustible liquids shall be installed close to the ceiling or beams or along walls not less than 1.8 m above the floor to protect it against mechanical damage. (2) Where practical, overhead piping referred to in Sentence (1) shall be supported from building framing members. (3) In buildings of steel frame construction, piping referred to in Sentence (1) shall be fastened to steel beams or columns by pipe hangers attached to the flanges. (4) Piping under concrete ceilings shall be suspended with the use of through bolts or expansion shields.",
