    subject: "Steam heating",
    contextLocation: "Ontario",
    constraintType: "Minimum",
    value: "(1) Flammable liquids and combustible liquid piping is permitted to be heated by steam lines provided the minimum steam temperature and pressure to make the liquid fluid are used and Sentences (2) and (3) are complied with. (2) A pressure regulator shall be provided in the steam line with a relief valve on the downstream side of the regulator. (3) Piping and steam lines shall be enclosed in insulation conforming to the Building Code.",
